00:22.861 --> 00:24.397
Help!

00:24.529 --> 00:25.595
Help!!

00:42.247 --> 00:43.779
Hi. I'm Maxine, and I'm an addict.

00:43.814 --> 00:45.397
Hi, Maxine.

00:45.460 --> 00:48.350
I haven't taken a pill
in 19 months and 5 days.

00:50.889 --> 00:54.991
But, um... but this...

00:55.026 --> 00:57.659
These past six days
have been really rough.

01:00.364 --> 01:02.931
Someone died at work, and, uh...

01:05.436 --> 01:09.838
I just have to remember
that this, too, shall pass.

01:13.511 --> 01:14.710
Thanks for coming.

01:14.745 --> 01:16.745
You used that line on Naomi last night?

01:16.781 --> 01:18.547
You figured that out fast.

01:18.582 --> 01:21.717
I spotted you two playing
tonsil hockey in your office.

01:21.752 --> 01:23.285
Is she as good as I remember?

01:24.021 --> 01:25.521
As a lawyer, of course.

01:25.556 --> 01:27.856
New case for you... Leo Scarlata.

01:27.892 --> 01:29.925
15 years into a life sentence

01:29.960 --> 01:32.027
for torching his family's restaurant.

01:32.062 --> 01:34.396
The fire killed one man,
injured another.

01:34.431 --> 01:35.730
Arson... Frankie will enjoy that.

01:35.765 --> 01:38.533
I don't see how it warrants
special delivery.

01:38.568 --> 01:40.435
Defense wanted to argue
diminished capacity,

01:40.470 --> 01:43.671
and the judge didn't allow it,
despite Leo's IQ being only 73.

01:43.706 --> 01:46.174
- A significant cognitive impairment.
- That, it is.

01:46.209 --> 01:48.676
That's exactly the kind of defendant
that gets bulldozed by the system.

01:48.711 --> 01:50.345
- Right again.
- Facts about the case?

01:50.380 --> 01:51.579
Solid, but not rock solid.

01:51.614 --> 01:53.015
Well, send the files to my office.

01:53.040 --> 01:54.449
Just one more thing.

01:54.717 --> 01:56.551
Meet Paul Slatkin.

01:56.586 --> 01:59.053
He's making a documentary
about Leo's incarceration.

01:59.088 --> 02:01.655
And, hopefully, exoneration.
It's a pleasure meeting you.

02:02.624 --> 02:04.724
This is my cameraman... Simon.

02:04.760 --> 02:06.560
They'll be filming your investigation.

02:06.595 --> 02:07.894
I am not spending five days

02:07.930 --> 02:09.696
with these gadflies
following my every move.

02:09.731 --> 02:11.298
You will if you want to work the case.

02:11.334 --> 02:12.166
I can help.

02:12.201 --> 02:13.934
I've been filming Leo and his family

02:13.970 --> 02:15.002
for the past two years.

02:15.037 --> 02:17.938
I've interviewed him,
his attorneys, family members.

02:17.974 --> 02:19.573
I can give you access to all of them.

02:19.608 --> 02:21.708
Great! Then you can stay
the hell away from Leo and me.

02:21.743 --> 02:23.944
This will be great publicity
for the CIU.

02:23.980 --> 02:25.075
Do you have the release?

02:25.100 --> 02:27.574
After the Dan Harris interview meltdown,
why would you even risk this?

02:27.599 --> 02:30.450
This time, the only ass truly
on the line is Leo Scarlata's.

02:30.485 --> 02:31.884
Even at your most self-sabotaging,

02:31.919 --> 02:33.416
you'd never hurt someone like him.

02:38.626 --> 02:41.494
You are so calculating
and manipulative and...

02:41.529 --> 02:43.496
- Right?
- That too.

02:43.531 --> 02:49.036
